  <ability>
    <abilitytitle>Hyperosmia</abilitytitle>
    <abilityid>magic.hyperosmia</abilityid>
    <abilityclass>Melee</abilityclass>
    <abilityattrmodifiers><attr>Perception</attr></abilityattrmodifiers>
    <abilitydescription>
      <p>
	The character gains a very enhanced sense of smell, temporarily.
	This spell gives them advantges to fighting when they cannot see
	(+2 to hit, more against strongly smelling opponents),
	+2 tracking, saves against illusions, +4 to Ambush roles, and +2 to Interogate and
	Perceive checks.  The spell lasts half an hour.
      </p>
    </abilitydescription>

    <abilitylevels>
      <abilitylevel>
        <levelnumber>1</levelnumber>
        <defaultlore>0</defaultlore>
        <defaultmartial>0</defaultmartial>
        <defaultgeneral>0</defaultgeneral>
        <defaultmagical>6</defaultmagical>
        <successes>2</successes>
        <attempts>1</attempts>
	<check>Magic Pool vs DDC 4</check>
	<overcharge>DC + 6</overcharge>
        <prereqabilitylevel>magic_school.wild_magic_1</prereqabilitylevel>		
      </abilitylevel>

      <abilitylevel>
        <levelnumber>2</levelnumber>
        <defaultlore>0</defaultlore>
        <defaultmartial>0</defaultmartial>
        <defaultgeneral>0</defaultgeneral>
        <defaultmagical>6</defaultmagical>
	<check>Magic Pool + 2 vs DDC 4</check>
	<overcharge>DC + 7</overcharge>
      </abilitylevel>      
    </abilitylevels>
  </ability>  



  <ability>
    <abilitytitle>Vermin Swarm</abilitytitle>
    <abilityid>magic.vermin_swarm</abilityid>
    <abilityclass>Melee</abilityclass>
    <abilityattrmodifiers><attr>Perception</attr></abilityattrmodifiers>
    <abilitydescription>
      <p>
	The character summons a swarm of vermin.  The GM should choose one 
	of the following types of swarms either randomly or as appropriate to
	the context: Spider, Beetle, Rat, Bees, Flys, Bats.  Swarms stay until
	the end of combat or 5 minutes which-ever is longer. 
      </p>

      <table>
	<tablecategory>Standard</tablecategory>
	<tablespec><fixed>0.3</fixed><fixed>0.6</fixed></tablespec>
	<tabletitle>Vermin Swarm Overcharge Table</tabletitle>
	<tablelabel>fig:vermin-swarm-overcharge</tablelabel>

	<tableheaderrow>
	  <td>Roll d88</td>
	  <td>Overcharge Effect</td>
	</tableheaderrow>

	<tablerow>
	  <td>11-28</td>
	  <td>The swarm mistakes the caster for the target.  They GM moves the swarm
	  towards the caster each turn until they are destroyed </td>
	</tablerow>

	<tablerow>
	  <td>31-38</td>
	  <td>The casters mind is linked to the swarm.  They can either banish the swarm
	  or control it, but that is all.
	  </td>
	</tablerow>

	<tablerow>
	  <td>41-58</td>
	  <td>Something from beyond takes a big bite out of the caster.  Caster suffers
	  3d6 damage.</td>
	</tablerow>

	<tablerow>
	  <td>61-88</td>
	  <td>Weirdness ensues.. Reroll on the Overcharge Effects Table..</td>
	</tablerow>	
      </table>
      
    </abilitydescription>

