  <ability>
    <abilitytitle>Therianthropy</abilitytitle>
    <abilityid>magic.therianthropy</abilityid>
    <abilityclass>Melee</abilityclass>
    <abilityattrmodifiers><attr>Willpower</attr></abilityattrmodifiers>
    <abilitydescription>
      <indexentry>Shapeshifting<subentry>see Therianthropy</subentry></indexentry>      
      <p>
	The caster takes animal form for up to a few hours.  The first
	time the caster casts the spell they roll on the Therianthropy
	table to choose the animal to which they are atuned.  That is the
	animal that they will always change into when casting this spell.
      </p>
      <!--
	  Therianthropy
	  differs from lycanthropy in that the caster
      -->

      <table>
	<tablecategory>Standard</tablecategory>
	<tablespec><fixed>0.3</fixed><fixed>0.6</fixed></tablespec>
	<tabletitle>Therianthropy Table</tabletitle>
	<tablelabel>fig:therianthropy</tablelabel>

	<tableheaderrow>
	  <td>Roll d88</td>
	  <td>Animal</td>
	</tableheaderrow>

	<tablerow> <td>11</td><td>Cockroach</td></tablerow>
	<tablerow> <td>12</td><td>Beetle</td></tablerow>
	<tablerow> <td>13-14</td><td>House fly or Firefly</td></tablerow>
	<tablerow> <td>15-18</td><td>Spider or Scorpion</td></tablerow>

	<tablerow> <td>21-22</td><td>Frog or Toad</td></tablerow>
	<tablerow> <td>23-25</td><td>Lizard or Newt</td></tablerow>
	<tablerow> <td>26</td><td>Squirrel, Mouse, Rat or Hamster</td></tablerow>
	<tablerow> <td>27</td><td>Mole, Vole or Hedgehog</td></tablerow>
	<tablerow> <td>28</td><td>Hare or Rabbit</td></tablerow>
	
	<tablerow> <td>31</td><td>Yak, Musk Ox, Bison, Bull or Cow</td></tablerow>
	<tablerow> <td>32-34</td><td>Sparrow, Crow, Parrot, Pidgeon</td></tablerow>
	<tablerow> <td>35-36</td><td>Weasel or Ferret</td></tablerow>
	<tablerow> <td>37-38</td><td>Bat</td></tablerow>

	<tablerow> <td>41</td><td>Deer, Elk</td></tablerow>
	<tablerow> <td>42-43</td><td>Goat or Ibex</td></tablerow>
	<tablerow> <td>44-45</td><td>Pig or Wild Boar</td></tablerow>	
	<tablerow> <td>46-47</td><td>Pony, Mule, Donkey or Draft Horse</td></tablerow>
	<tablerow> <td>48</td><td>Python</td></tablerow>
	
	<tablerow> <td>51-52</td><td>Fox or Jackal</td></tablerow>
	<tablerow> <td>53-54</td><td>Owl or Vulture</td></tablerow>
	<tablerow> <td>55</td><td>Baboon, Gibbon, Orangutan or Chimpanzee</td></tablerow>
	<tablerow> <td>56-58</td><td>Mastiff, Terrier, Sheepdog, Scent Hound, Lapdog, Retriever</td></tablerow>
	
	<tablerow> <td>61-63</td><td>House Cat</td></tablerow>
	<tablerow> <td>64-65</td><td>Crocodile</td></tablerow>
	<tablerow> <td>66-68</td><td>Hawk</td></tablerow>
	
	<tablerow> <td>71-72</td><td>Otter or Badger</td></tablerow>
	<tablerow> <td>73-74</td><td>Wolverine</td></tablerow>
	<tablerow> <td>75</td><td>Thorough-bred Horse</td></tablerow>
	<tablerow> <td>76-78</td><td>Viper (poisonous)</td></tablerow>
	
	<tablerow> <td>81-83</td><td>Wolf</td></tablerow>
	<tablerow> <td>84</td><td>Gorilla</td></tablerow>
	<tablerow> <td>85-86</td><td>Lion, Snow Leopard, Panther etc.</td></tablerow>
	<tablerow> <td>87-88</td><td>Bear Black, Brown or Polar</td></tablerow>
      </table>

      <p>
	If a character rolls one of the results with multiple animals then it
	is the GMs role to choose which of the animals the caster becomes based
	on their character and the environs from which they came, <eg/> a northern
	barbarian might become a polar bear given the bear result.	
      </p>
     

      <table>
	<tablecategory>Standard</tablecategory>
	<tablespec><fixed>0.3</fixed><fixed>0.6</fixed></tablespec>
	<tabletitle>Therianthropy Overcharge Table</tabletitle>
	<tablelabel>fig:therianthropy_overcharge</tablelabel>

	<tableheaderrow>
	  <td>Roll d88</td>
	  <td>ThaOvercharge Effect</td>
	</tableheaderrow>

	<tablerow> <td>13-14</td><td>Roll on the random overcharge table</td></tablerow>
	<tablerow> <td>14-18</td><td>The character is trapped in the animal form until the spell can be removed.</td></tablerow>
	<tablerow> <td>21-28</td><td>The caster is trapped in animal form for d3 days or until the spell is removed.</td></tablerow>
	<tablerow> <td>31-58</td><td>The character gains an aspect that their animal might have.</td></tablerow>
	<tablerow> <td>61-88</td><td>No Effect</td></tablerow>
      </table>

      <p>
	In the event the spell is overcharged roll on the table above.
      </p>
    </abilitydescription>

